history.content:
FEMTech is Cal's first all-majors club for women interested in technology. FEMTech promotes diversity and inspires women from all majors to excel in technology careers. 

 

FEMTech Launch is a program that provides office hours, extra help, and tutoring sessions specifically geared towards underrepresented minorities in lower level CS courses. We're looking for motivated, passionate people that are interested in teaching and guiding less experienced students in the lower division CS classes. You will be working in a team of 2 tutors focused on helping 5-7 students, as well as providing office hours for your students. As a tutor, you will also have access to all of FEMTech's resources including direct connections to companies such as Google, Snapchat, and Facebook.

 

If you're interested in applying please fill out this application: http://tinyurl.com/launchtutorf18

 

Any questions or concerns can be directed to femtechlaunch@gmail.com

 

Thank you!
history.subject: FEMTech Launch Tutor Opportunity

history.content:
Hello!

If you are struggling in the lower division CS classes, please consider to be a student for FEMTech Launch! Our tutoring sections are small, with a size of 5-7 students per section, and we aim to build a community of like-minded students passionate about CS. If you have ever felt lost in class due to the overwhelming number of people, please consider applying as FEMTech Launch not only offers academic support, but also career and mental health guidance. 

If you are interested in applying as a student, please go here: http://tinyurl.com/launchf18

On the other hand, if you loved the material from CS 61A, CS 61B, or CS 70, please consider applying to be a tutor for FEMTech Launch. We are dedicated to motivating and assisting underrepresented minorities in the lower division CS classes, and our goal is to build communities that make their journey at Berkeley more rewarding. Tutors are paired together to head sections of around 5-7 students. Not only will you gain invaluable teaching experience, but you will also be part of a close-knit community committed to help guide students at Berkeley.

Please consider applying here if interested: http://tinyurl.com/launchtutorf18

Any questions or concerns can be directed to femtechlaunch@gmail.com

Thanks!
